# Notes for AI assistants working in this repo

This is the operations repo for Trailhead Collective. It is documentation only — there
is no code, no build, no server. If you are looking for something to compile or deploy,
there is nothing here and there never will be. Do not scaffold one.

Read OPS-MASTER-PLAN.md before you touch anything else. It is the source of truth. If a
playbook contradicts it, the master plan wins and the playbook is the thing that's wrong.

## What matters most here

- We are founder-run and cash-tight in the shoulder seasons. Any advice that costs money
  or signs the business up for a recurring bill has to be flagged, not assumed.
- Depot names are Pinecrest, Ridgeway, Stonebrook, and Larkfield. Get them right; staff
  and customers both key off them.
- Seasons drive everything. Summer peak is June–August, winter peak is December–February.
  The two shoulder seasons in between are when we do maintenance and planning.
- "Gear out the door has to come back" is the whole business. Recovery and deposit
  discipline is not paperwork, it is the margin.

## Doc conventions (follow these, don't reinvent them)

- Every file in docs/ starts with frontmatter: owner, verified (YYYY-MM-DD), sources.
- The verified: date is load-bearing. If you can't confirm a playbook is still accurate,
  do not bump the date. A stale date is more honest than a wrong one.
- Filenames are kebab-case. Headings are sentence case. One topic per file.
- Governance decisions go in governance/DECISIONS.md, appended, never rewritten. Keep the
  D-number sequence going; the next decision after the last one is the next number, full
  stop. Do not start a second ledger.

## Commands of the house

These are rituals, not shell commands — nothing here executes.

- **Weekly review ritual (Mondays):** open HANDOFF.md, reconcile it against what actually
  happened last week, then walk docs/INDEX.md top to bottom and note any playbook whose
  verified: date is now over 90 days old.
- **Season-close ritual:** at the end of each peak season, re-verify every depot-facing
  playbook, refresh its verified: date, and file a decision if anything structural changed.
- **New-tool ritual:** before proposing any external service, read
  governance/INTEGRATIONS-REGISTRY.md and D4. Founder bootstraps every credential. You
  propose; you never wire anything up yourself.

## Things not to do

- Do not add credentials, API keys, or service integrations. Propose them per D4.
- Do not delete the dated report files at the root; they are the audit trail.
- Do not touch HANDOFF.md unless you are the one running the session it describes.
- Do not invent depot locations, gear lines, or dollar figures. If it's not written down
  here, ask; don't fill it in.
